How to install Codegence Aurora:
===============================

Requeriments:
-------------
- g++ >= 4.8 ( gcc-c++ package )
- Poco >= 1.6 - http://pocoproject.org/
- jsoncpp >= 0.6 - http://jsoncpp.sourceforge.net/
- boost xpressive >= 1.57 - ( boost-devel package or libboost-dev depending on distribution )
- cmake >= 3.2
- make >= 4.0

Compiling:
----------
1) get into "bin/main" create the directory if needed:
    mkdir -p bin/main; cd bin/main
2) run cmake with debug enabled:
    cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug ../../prj/main
3) run make, use multiple threads with the "-j" parameter:
    make -j8

Running:
--------
After compiling in "bin/main".
1) get into "res/priv":
    cd res/priv
2) run the ejecutable
    ../../bin/main/codegence-aurora
3) it will run as a daemon. to stop it you need to send the SIGTERM signal or CTRL-C.


glhf
